ABOUT US

Shibasonic is a unique play to earn game with crypto integration taking themes from both Shibarium's rise in popularity with it's release along with Sonic being quite popular in terms of how the trend of "Harrypotterobamasonic10inu" became the catch to many hitting well over 100million marketcap.

WHITEPAPER

Play to Earn

Shibasonic is a unique play to earn game Play-to-earn games (P2E) do what most traditional video games don't, Reward players for their time and effort spent in the game. After all, the players who can complete tasks faster and more effectively are rewarded according.

What sets Shibasonic - Play To Earn apart from other mobile games is its unique earning feature. As you progress through the game and collect coins, you have the opportunity to convert them into real money. This means that not only are you having fun and improving your gaming skills, but you're also earning money in the process.

Whether you're a casual gamer looking for a fun and engaging way to pass the time or a serious gamer who wants to earn real money, Shibasonic - Play To Earn has something for everyone.

With its intuitive controls, fast-paced gameplay, and exciting earning potential, this game is sure to become a favorite among mobile gamers everywhere.

Roadmap

WEBSITE LAUNCH

Develop and launch an official Shibasonic website to provide information about the project, its features, and the P2E Game.

AUDIT

Conduct a comprehensive smart contract audit to ensure the security and reliability of the gaming platform.

GAME RELEASE

Launch of the P2E Shibasonic game.

LISTING ON COINMARKETCAP (CMC) AND COINGECKO (CG)

Apply for and secure listings on popular cryptocurrency data platforms such as CoinMarketCap and CoinGecko to increase visibility and market exposure.

PARTNERSHIP WITH INFLUENCERS

Collaborate with influential figures in the blockchain and gaming industries to promote Shibasonic, raise awareness, and attract a wider user base.

COMMUNITY BUILDING

Engage with the community through social media platforms, online forums, and Discord channels, fostering an active and supportive community around Shibasonic.
